        <p data-uuid="5080efa868cf4a3793827632f934c84b">Abolition was just one of the many reform movements that arose in the United States. The religious revival called the Second Great Awakening triggered a wave of reform efforts. Some people supported the <dfn title="temperance movement">temperance movement</dfn>, which tried to stop alcohol abuse. They blamed alcohol for problems of society such as crime and poverty.</p>
